title: Missiles from Hell - Battle of the V-1 [1958 - UK] WWII drama
description: Missiles from Hell [1958 - UK] original title Battle of the V-1 Drama / War starring . . . . Michael Rennie, Patricia Medina, Christopher Lee http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0051402/ The story of a Polish Resistance group which discovers details of the manufacture of the German V-1 Flying Bomb at Peenemünde in 1943. Liaising with service chiefs in London, the group manage to pass on enough information to convince them to launch a bombing raid. In the climax to the film, they attempt to steal a V-1 which lands in a field during testing. In the opening credits are an extract from Winston Churchill's Parliamentary Statement made on 6 July 1944.
